{"id":1979,"date":"2023-05-31T15:27:13","date_gmt":"2023-05-31T12:27:13","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.nla.ae\/?page_id=1979"},"modified":"2023-05-31T15:27:25","modified_gmt":"2023-05-31T12:27:25","slug":"accessibility","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.nla.ae\/en\/accessibility\/","title":{"rendered":"Accessibility"},"content":{"rendered":"<h2>Accessibility<\/h2>\n<p>As part of its effort to facilitate access to information and services through its website, National Library and Archives had designed its website with a set of features that help users, especially those with special needs, to access required information or services in an easy and quick manner.<br \/>\nFeatures that help easy browsing of the website include:<br \/>\n\u2022\u00a0\u00a0 \u00a0Sitemap<br \/>\n\u2022\u00a0\u00a0 \u00a0Text-to-speech<br \/>\n\u2022\u00a0\u00a0 \u00a0Zoom in screen<br \/>\n\u2022\u00a0\u00a0 \u00a0Change font size<br \/>\n\u2022\u00a0\u00a0 \u00a0Alternative texts for images<\/p>\n<h2>Sitemap<\/h2>\n<p>National Library and Archives follows the international W3C Standards in designing and structuring its website, making it easy to browse and access all its information and services.<\/p>\n<h2>Text-To-Speech<\/h2>\n<p>National Library and Archives website provides the text-to-speech feature for users with special needs or visually impaired. The feature can be used by clicking on the &#8220;Listen to this page&#8221; icon on top of the page.<\/p>\n<h2>Zoom In Screen<\/h2>\n<p>When facing difficulty in reading texts or viewing images, users can use the zoom-in feature from the View menu on their browsers and adjust screen size.<\/p>\n<h2>Change Font Size<\/h2>\n<p>If you find it difficult to read the text on your screen, you may increase\/decrease the font size by clicking on the (+A) or (-A) icons on top of the page. You may, as well, change the font size using your browser&#8217;s tools.<\/p>\n<h2>Alternative Text For Images<\/h2>\n<p>Each image on National Library and Archives website is tagged with appropriate description. Users can view the description by positioning the mouse cursor over the image.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Accessibility As part of its effort to facilitate access to information and services through its website, National Library and Archives had designed its website with a set of features that help users, especially those with special needs, to access required information or services in an easy and quick manner. Features that help easy browsing of [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"templates\/template-with-banner.php","meta":{"inline_featured_image":false,"footnotes":""},"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.nla.ae\/en\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/1979"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.nla.ae\/en\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.nla.ae\/en\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.nla.ae\/en\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.nla.ae\/en\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=1979"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.nla.ae\/en\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/1979\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.nla.ae\/en\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=1979"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}